TEXT(beginproblem());

Context("LimitedNumeric");

$yd1 = random(15,30,1);
$ft1 = $yd1*3;
$yd2 = random(3,14,1);
$ft2 = $yd2*3;

##############################################

BEGIN_PGML

It's given that [` 1 \text{ yard} = 3 \text{ feet} `]. Do the following unit conversions.

a.  [`` [$yd1] \text{ yards} = ``] [__________]{$ft1} [`` \text{ feet} ``]

b. [`` [$ft2] \text{ feet} = ``] [__________]{$yd2} [`` \text{ yards} ``]

END_PGML


